The code for `clk_get_rate()` in the Linux Common Clock Framework (CCF) can vary depending on the specific version of the Linux kernel and the clock driver in use. However, below is a generalized example of how `clk_get_rate()` might be implemented in the CCF:

```c
unsigned long clk_get_rate(struct clk *clk)
{
    struct clk_hw *hw;
    unsigned long rate;

    if (!clk || IS_ERR(clk))
        return 0;

    hw = to_clk_hw(clk);
    if (!hw)
        return 0;

    rate = clk_hw_get_rate(hw);

    return rate;
}
```

